6:
You're sure?! Like, reeeally sure?! 
Really, really, reeeeeeally sure?!
9:
Dead sure! 
I can feel it in my whiskers, man!
11:
Same! My feline instincts are telling me 
this is the spot!
15:
Dude, that's AWESOME! 
We've finally found it! 
That black gloop is gonna change how 
we power EVERYTHING!
16:
C'mon guys, we've gotta get back to 
the village! Wait 'til everyone hears! 
We've gotta prep for the big dig!
19:
All right, dudes! 
Let Operation: Burny Gloop begin!
25:
Chief, we've been playing along with all 
your big talk about new energy 
because of the potential it had for US, 
the catfolk.
26:
You're supposed to be on OUR side, 
looking out for OUR people! 
Who are those mutts?!
29:
They're part of the team. 
The catfolk are in charge of research 
and scouting, and the dogfolk are 
going to manage the excavation.
32:
Yer out of yer mind, sonny! 
That fancy gloop of yers would be 
better off in the ground than the 
clutches of DOGS!
34:
They're just stringing you along to steal 
the gloop, boy! 
A real chief would see right through 
those mangy dogs!
44:
Yeah, well. 
That chatterbox isn't chief for nothing. 
Watch.
50: All right, everyone quiet down for a sec!
52:
Dude, I hear you. 
You guys are excited for the new power, 
and you're worried that the dogfolk will 
take it away.
55:
Exactly! 
We're the ones who found it, 
so it belongs to us!
58:
Do you propose we excavate the 
premises on our own? 
I would remind you; we lack the 
technology and workforce to do so 
efficiently.
61:
It's not feasible. 
What we DO have is information! 
A valuable resource, albeit a 
temporary one.
63:
That information will inevitably pass to 
the dogfolk, and when it does, they'll 
have the means to excavate, but no 
obligation to share.
69:
Conversely, if we pool our resources 
with the dogfolk, both our peoples will 
reap the benefits—hot meals! Warm 
beds!
71:
I recognize that we've only just closed 
the chapter on a long and bitter war. 
You don't have to like the dogfolk...
74:
But I ask for your trust! 
Not in the dogfolk, but in the 
opportunities they present us! 
The burny gloop will rejuvenate these 
lands!
77:
Think of your children! Their children! 
Okay? C'mon, man, I'm begging you 
guys here!
81:
...Y'know, I think Claw has a point. That 
burny gloop stuff is gonna be so cool!
83:
Yeah. The dogfolk agreed to the truce 
same as we did. If we can't get along 
now, what was the truce even for?
85:
Oi, cat—I mean... 
You over there, may I ask your name?
87:
Huh? Me? I'm Callie! Callie the calico! 
This tabby over here is Travis.
89:
Callie and Travis, eh? 
I'm Frantz. Would you two like to join our 
team?
91:
Wait, you mean the dogfolk team? 
Are you sure?
92:
Course, mate. 
You lot'll have a BLAST learning how to 
use saltpeter. Heh.
99: Man, sorry you guys had to see that!
102:
You were really cool though, Claw! 
I can't believe you managed to 
convince everyone that easily.
105:
Nah, I'm not so sure about that. 
It's great they're going along with the 
plan, but they still looked reluctant to 
me.
109:
Guys like them aren't interested in 
reason.
113:
You said it, Bro. 
I've sure had my paws full as chief.
115:
But, y'know? 
The war really wore those poor old farts 
thin. They don't have the energy left to 
try new things.
119:
Me, though? Dude, I've got enough 
energy for all of 'em!
121:
I'll put smiles on those crochety old faces! On EVERYONE'S faces! 
I'm meeting with the dogfolk's dig team 
first thing tomorrow!
124:
Operation: Burny Gloop will be our very 
first joint project with the dogfolk! 
We'll rebuild our village—and our 
relationship!
